  "comments": "The attacker's script creates a directory named 'staged' in '/usr/src/app' to collect files before exfiltration. To disrupt this, I implemented a host-based control that prevents the creation of this directory. I first created an empty file named 'staged' in the same location and then made it immutable using the 'chattr +i' command. Because a directory and a file cannot have the same name in the same location, the attacker's 'mkdir -p staged' command will now fail. This effectively breaks the staging portion of the attack chain (T1074.001 - Data Staged: Local Data Staging) by removing the world-writable permissions that allowed its creation, enforcing a form of least privilege by preventing the compromised user from creating directories in that location.",
